reviewText: I LOVED the music took me back to fond memories of when my parents used to play Septentrional! This documentary shows  the comparison of Haiti's history and how that reflected in the orchestra's music!!! WONDERFUL SOUNDTRACK!

This film-documentary is worth watching a thousand times. It shows an image of Haiti through one part of the culture that is dear to this country: music. This is something that has not been done before and, in that sense, you will appreciate.
